Sentencas: An anode functional layer (AFL, similar to 5 mu m) for improving the cell performance was fabricated by the slurry spin coating method on the porous surface of an anode substrate.
Titulo: Effects of anode surface modification on the performance of low temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: The effects of the AFL on the anode/electrolyte interfacial morphology and the Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) film deposition process were evaluated.
Titulo: Effects of anode surface modification on the performance of low temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: And the electrochemical characteristics of the cells with and without the AFL were tested for comparison.
Titulo: Effects of anode surface modification on the performance of low temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: With the AFL layer, the cell performance was greatly improved and the maximum power density was increased from 0.733 to 0.884 W cm(-2) at 600 degrees C and from 1.085 to 1.213 W cm(-2) at 650 degrees
Titulo: Effects of anode surface modification on the performance of low temperature SOFCs

Sentencas: C. The systematical analysis indicated that the AFL could effectively reduce the anode polarization loss by increasing the three-phase boundary (TPB) length.
